ACCOLADES:

2023: Cape Cod League All-Star

FRESHMAN (2023):

Pitched in 24 games, finishing 2-5 with a 6.34 ERA…made eight starts, striking out 49 batters in 44.0 innings…part of a triple play at No. 8 TCU (2/25), FSU’s first turned triple play since 2009…season-high 5.1 innings pitched against No. 1 Wake Forest (5/14)…struck out six Demon Deacons, a season-high…made his first career start and appearance opening weekend against James Madison (2/19)…earned first win against Pitt (3/10), recording the final two outs before FSU’s walk-off win…also beat Virginia Tech (4/23) with 3.0 shutout innings…did not allow a hit in 3.0 innings against USF (3/1)…pitched a scoreless inning in relief at Louisville (5/20)…was a Cape Cod League All-Star for Hyannis Harbor Hawks, finishing with a 2.94 ERA and 21 strikeouts over 18.1 innings pitched.

PERSONAL:Graduated from Jesuit High in Tampa…ranked the No. 4 left-handed pitcher in Florida and No. 258 nationally by Perfect Game…helped Jesuit win the 5A state championship as a senior, finishing 7-3 with 91 strikeouts and a 2.02 ERA over 66.0 innings pitched…struck out seven batters in five scoreless innings in the state semifinals against Naples…high school teammates with Ryan Denison…named an All-813Preps 2A-5A first team selection his senior year…also played basketball in high school…committed to Florida State in October 2019…parents are Jimmy and Dawn Arnold…brother Grayson and sister Caroline…dad played football at UCF…majoring in sport management…born on March 21, 2004.
